# Spacewalk Operations Runbook

Operational procedures for an Oracle Spacewalk (Oracle Linux Manager) server: relocating the package store onto NFS, recovering the jabberd database after corruption, wiring up ULN credentials for repo sync, and the console workflow for channels, repositories, and activation keys.

> Hostnames, IPs, and account paths below are generic placeholders.

## Relocate the package store to an NFS volume

Stop the service and stage the existing package directory off the mount point:


spacewalk-service stop
mv /var/satellite/redhat /home/opsadmin/


Add the NFS volume to `/etc/fstab`:


# NFS volume for Spacewalk packages
10.0.0.50:/export/swalk  /var/satellite  nfs  rw,bg,hard,nointr,rsize=65536,wsize=65536,tcp,nfsvers=3,timeo=600,actimeo=700,acregmin=3,lock,suid


Install the NFS client tools (set an http proxy first if one isn't configured in `/etc/yum.conf`):

rpm -qa | grep nfs

cd /etc/yum.repos.d/
cp -p public-yum-ol6.repo.rpmsave public-yum-ol6.repo

# Set a proxy only if not already defined in /etc/yum.conf
export http_proxy=http://10.0.0.30:3128   # Site A
# or
export http_proxy=http://10.0.0.31:3128   # Site B

yum install nfs-utils
rm -f public-yum-ol6.repo

Mount the volume and restore the package directory with the correct ownership:

service rpcbind start
mount /var/satellite/
df -h

mv /home/opsadmin/redhat /var/satellite/
ls -l /var/

chown apache:root /var/satellite
chown apache:root /var/satellite/redhat

chkconfig rpcbind --list
chkconfig rpcbind on

spacewalk-service start

## Recover a corrupted jabberd database

### Symptom

`osa-dispatcher` fails to start and the service start reports a jabberd error:


# spacewalk-service start
Starting spacewalk services...
Initializing jabberd processes ...
Starting router:                                           [  OK  ]
Starting sm:                                               [  OK  ]
Starting c2s:                                              [  OK  ]
Starting s2s:                                              [  OK  ]
Starting tomcat6:                                          [  OK  ]
Waiting for tomcat to be ready ...
Starting httpd:                                            [  OK  ]
Starting osa-dispatcher: ('Not able to reconnect - See https://access.redhat.com/solutions/45332 for possible solutions.\n',)
('Error caught:',)
ERROR: unhandled exception occurred: (can't write str to text stream).
                                                           [FAILED]
Starting rhn-search...
Starting cobbler daemon:                                   [  OK  ]
Starting RHN Taskomatic...
Done.


The root cause shows up in the system log:


$ sudo grep 'corruption detected' /var/log/messages
... spacewalk01 jabberd/sm[3203]: db: corruption detected! close all jabberd processes and run db_recover

### Fix — switch jabberd from Berkeley DB to SQLite

Stop the service:

spacewalk-service stop

Back up `sm.xml` and change `<driver>db</driver>` to `<driver>sqlite</driver>`:

cp -p /etc/jabberd/sm.xml sm.xml.$(date +%F).bak
vim /etc/jabberd/sm.xml
diff /etc/jabberd/sm.xml sm.xml.$(date +%F).bak

Back up `c2s.xml` and change `<module>db</module>` to `<module>sqlite</module>`:


cp -p /etc/jabberd/c2s.xml c2s.xml.$(date +%F).bak
vim /etc/jabberd/c2s.xml
diff /etc/jabberd/c2s.xml c2s.xml.$(date +%F).bak


Create the SQLite database and set ownership:

sqlite3 /var/lib/jabberd/db/sqlite.db < /usr/share/jabberd/db-setup.sqlite
chown jabber:jabber /var/lib/jabberd/db/sqlite.db


Start and verify:


spacewalk-service start
spacewalk-service status


> **Reference:** <https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E92593_01/E85212/html/swk26-jabberd.html>

## Add ULN credentials for repo sync

Check the config file (it should be root-readable only):


ls -l /etc/rhn/spacewalk-repo-sync/uln.conf
# -r-------- 1 root root ... /etc/rhn/spacewalk-repo-sync/uln.conf


Temporarily grant write access, add the ULN single sign-on credentials, then revoke write access:

chmod 600 /etc/rhn/spacewalk-repo-sync/uln.conf
vim /etc/rhn/spacewalk-repo-sync/uln.conf

[main]
username=<ULN_SSO_username>
password=<ULN_SSO_password>

chmod 400 /etc/rhn/spacewalk-repo-sync/uln.conf

## Console workflows

| Task | Navigation |
|------|------------|
| Create a parent channel | Channels → Manage Software Channels → Create Channel |
| Create a child channel | Channels → Manage Software Channels → Create Channel |
| Create a repo (ULN repo URL) | Channels → Manage Software Channels → Manage Repositories → Create Repository |
| Create a repo (public yum URL) | Channels → Manage Software Channels → Manage Repositories → Create Repository |
| Point a repo to a channel | Channels → Manage Software Channels → *(select channel)* → Repositories → *(select repo)* → Update Repositories |
| Sync a repo | Channels → Manage Software Channels → *(select channel)* → Repositories → Sync → Sync Now |
| Create an activation key | Systems → Activation Keys → Create Key |